{% include 'layouts/partials/header.njk' %}

<section id="intro" class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-2 mb-2">
    <div class="gap-6">
        <p>
            <span class="text-lg font-sans font-semibold">Hi, I'm Ed Marsh</span>. My job title has always been <a href="/skills/technical-writing">technical writer</a>, but I've made complex information accessible for over three decades by incorporating <a href="/skills/information-architecture/">information architecture</a>, <a href="/skills/content-strategy">content strategy</a>, and <a href="/skills/community">community building</a>.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-6">I'm passionate about clear, concise, and consistent content. I'm opinionated about the Oxford comma. I specialize in building or revamping documentation practices. My process involves:</p>

        <ul class="list-inside">
            <li>Assessing your current content situation.</li>
            <li>Defining structure.</li>
            <li>Implementing <a href="skills/content-strategy">content strategy</a>.</li>
            <li><a href="skills/community">Engaging the people</a> in your organization who are passionate about content.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-6">This site is my portfolio. I <a href="/static-site-transformation">rebuilt it from the ground up</a> to show how I can work with developers and stakeholders to help organizations with all aspects of their content.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-48">
        <img
            src="/assets/images/ed-marsh.jpg"
            alt="Ed Marsh, photo courtesy Arclight Images"
            title="Ed Marsh, photo courtesy Arclight Images"
            class="rounded-lg"
        >
    </div>
</section>

{% set collectionName = "skills" %}
<section class="mx-auto rounded-2xl border border-jet-900 p-6" id="{{collectionName}}">
    <h2>How I can help you</h2>
    <p class="text-jet-100">Here are the biggest ways I can help your organization. <a href="/skills/">See all the ways I can help</a>.</p>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2">
        {% set featured = collections[collectionName] | filterBy("data.featured", true) %}
        {% set sortedFeatured = featured | sort(false, false, "data.featuredOrder") %}
        {% for item in sortedFeatured %}
            {% if loop.index0 < 4 %}
                {% include 'layouts/partials/card.njk' %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>

{% set collectionName = "blog" %}
<section class="mt-6" id="{{collectionName}}" style="border: 1px solid var(--bg-jet-900); border-radius: 1rem; padding:6px;">
    <h2 class="px-3">Blog- Creating a static site</h2>
    <p class="description px-3 text-jet-100">I updated and simplified my old WordPress site using the <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/">Eleventy static site generator</a>. Here's how I can use the lessons learned to help you meet your content goals. <span class="col-span-full text-lg font-bold italic">
            <a href="/static-site-transformation/">Check back frequently to read the full series!</a></span></p>
    <div class="grid col-auto sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2 px-3">
        {% set featured = collections[collectionName] | filterBy("data.featured", true) %}
        {% set sortedFeatured = featured | sort(false, false, "data.featuredOrder") %}
        {% for item in sortedFeatured %}
            {% if loop.index0 < 4 %}
                {% include 'layouts/partials/card.njk' %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>

{% set collectionName = "podcasts" %}
<section class="mt-6" id="{{collectionName}}"  style="border: 1px solid var(--bg-jet-900); border-radius: 1rem; padding:6px;">
    <h2 class="px-3">Recent podcasts</h2>
    <p class="description px-3 text-jet-100">I'm the jack-of-all-trades for the <a href="podcasts/">Content Content podcast</a>, where I interview &ldquo;the people behind the content&rdquo; in technical communication, content strategy, content marketing, implementation, and more.
   Check out <span class="text-lg italic">
            <a href="/podcasts/">all of the amazing people I spoke with.</a>
        </span>
    </p>
    <div class="grid col-auto sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2 px-3">

        {% set filtered_collections = collections.podcasts %}
        {% for item in filtered_collections | reverse %}
            {% if loop.index0 <= 3 %}
                {% include 'layouts/partials/card.njk' %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}

    </div>
</section>

{% include 'layouts/partials/footer.njk' %}